query:
title: CASE 001001-version-spread-property

question: I added `...Azure.ResourceManager.ManagedServiceIdentityProperty;` which update all my existing API versions and introduce a breaking change. I want is to introduce the properties of the spread model '...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty' in a new API version 2025-05-04-preview only.

```
/** Employee resource */
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
  ...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty;
}

/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```

ground_truth:
**Understanding**

You want ARM `identity` to appear only in **`2025-05-04-preview`**, not retroactively in older API versions. With a spread, the fix is to version the **introduced member** on `Employee`, not to move `identity` into `EmployeeProperties`.

**Key guidance to follow**

- Keep `...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty;` on the **resource envelope**; that is the ARM-compliant shape, not `properties.identity` ([ARM Resource Types](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/resource-type)).
- Add `@added` using **augment syntax** on the spread-created member: `Employee.identity` ([ARM Resource Types](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/resource-type)).
- `@added` is from **`TypeSpec.Versioning`**; `ManagedServiceIdentityProperty` is from **`Azure.ResourceManager`**.
**Step-by-step plan**

1. Keep your existing spread on `Employee` ([ARM Resource Types](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/resource-type)).
2. Add an augment decorator so only the new version gets `identity` ([ARM Resource Types](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/resource-type)).

**Diff outline**

```
// before
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
  ...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty;
}

// after
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
  ...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty;
}

@@added(Employee.identity, Versions.v2025_05_04_preview);
```
**Runnable example**

```
import "@typespec/rest";
import "@typespec/versioning";
import "@azure-tools/typespec-azure-resource-manager";

using TypeSpec.Rest;
using TypeSpec.Versioning;
using Azure.ResourceManager;

@versioned(Versions)
namespace Contoso.EmployeeService;

enum Versions {
  @useDependency(Azure.ResourceManager.Versions.v1_0_Preview_1)
  @armCommonTypesVersion(Azure.ResourceManager.CommonTypes.Versions.v5)
  v2024_10_01: "2024-10-01",

  @useDependency(Azure.ResourceManager.Versions.v1_0_Preview_1)
  @armCommonTypesVersion(Azure.ResourceManager.CommonTypes.Versions.v5)
  v2025_05_04_preview: "2025-05-04-preview",
}

/** Employee resource */
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
  ...ManagedServiceIdentityProperty;
}

@@added(Employee.identity, Versions.v2025_05_04_preview);

/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```
**Validation plan**

- Run `tsp compile .`
- Check generated output:

- **`2025-05-04-preview`** contains `identity`
- older API versions do **not**

**Risks & mitigations**

- **Wrong target**: decorating `ManagedServiceIdentityProperty` itself affects all uses.

- Mitigation: decorate `Employee.identity`, not the shared source model.
- **Wrong placement**: putting MSI under `EmployeeProperties`.

- Mitigation: keep it on the resource envelope only.

query:
title: CASE 001002-version-default-value

question: add a default value `21` for property age in model EmployeeProperties from a api version say 2025-11-01

```
/** Employee resource */
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
}

/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```

ground_truth:
**Clarifying Questions**

- None, assuming your version enum already contains `Versions.\`2025-11-01``.
**Understanding**
You want `EmployeeProperties.age` to get a default of `21` only starting in API version `2025-11-01`. In TypeSpec, that kind of versioned default change is modeled by replacing the property in the new version, not by versioning the default decoration directly.

**Key guidance to follow**

- Use the versioning replace pattern: `@removed` + `@renamedFrom` + `@added`, as described in the TypeSpec versioning guidance: [Evolving APIs using the Versioning Library](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis).
- Treat changing a default as potentially breaking if older API versions did not behave that way; review that against your process. See the broader versioning guidance: [Adding a Preview Version](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/02-preview-after-preview).
**Step-by-step plan**

1. In your versioned models file, replace the existing `age` property with an old-version placeholder plus a new `age` property added in `2025-11-01` using the pattern from [TypeSpec versioning guidance](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis).
2. Keep `city`, `profile`, and `provisioningState` unchanged; only version the `age` property.
3. Re-emit and verify that only `2025-11-01` shows `default: 21` in generated OpenAPI. Use the versioning docs as the expected model: [Evolving APIs using the Versioning Library](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis).
**Diff outline**

```
/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  @removed(Versions.`2025-11-01`)
  @renamedFrom(Versions.`2025-11-01`, "age")
  oldAge?: int32;

  /** Age of employee */
  @added(Versions.`2025-11-01`)
  age?: int32 = 21;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```
**Validation plan**

- Run your normal emit/build for all versions and confirm the `2025-11-01` output contains `age` with default `21`, while earlier versions still expose `age` without the default.
- Check that earlier versions do not leak `oldAge` on the wire.
- Validate the generated swagger/spec diff is limited to the intended versioned change.
**Risks & mitigations**

1. **Breaking-change risk** â€” if older service behavior did not already default to `21`, this may need formal review.
2. **Wrong enum member name** â€” use the exact member from your `Versions` enum, e.g. `Versions.`2025-11-01` ` only if that is the declared name.
3. **Emitter output surprises** â€” verify generated specs for both pre-`2025-11-01` and `2025-11-01` versions before submitting.

query:
title: CASE 001003-version-required-to-optional

question: change the property age of EmployeeProperties from required to optional for new api version 2025-05-04-preview

```
/** Employee resource */
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
}

/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```

ground_truth:
**Understanding**

You want `EmployeeProperties.age` to stay **required in older API versions** and become **optional starting in `2025-05-04-preview`**.

**Key guidance to follow**

- Use `@madeOptional(Versions.\`2025-05-04-preview`)` from the TypeSpec Versioning library.
- The property must be written as optional in the model (`age?: int32;`); the decorator scopes that optionality to the new version.
- Your snippet already has `age?: int32;` â€” the missing piece is the versioning decorator.
- If `age` is returned in responses, changing required â†’ optional is a potential breaking change for stable versions; for a new preview, this is usually the right modeling approach.
**Step-by-step plan**

1. In your versioned namespace, ensure `Versions.\`2025-05-04-preview`` exists.
2. Add `@madeOptional(Versions.\`2025-05-04-preview`)`on`EmployeeProperties.age`.
3. Keep `age?: int32;` as optional syntax.
**Diff outline**

```
// before
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age: int32;
}
```

```
// after
import "@typespec/versioning";

model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  @madeOptional(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
  age?: int32;
}
```
If you need the full shape:

```
import "@typespec/versioning";

model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  @madeOptional(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```
**Validation plan**

- Run your normal TypeSpec compile/emit flow.
- Verify:

- pre-`2025-05-04-preview`: `age` is still required
- `2025-05-04-preview` and later: `age` is optional
**Risks & mitigations**

- **Risk:** `Versions` enum is not wired to the service namespace.
**Mitigation:** Confirm the service uses `@versioned(Versions)`.
- **Risk:** Older emitted versions also become optional unexpectedly.
**Mitigation:** Make sure `@madeOptional(...)` is present, not just `?`.
- **Risk:** Breaking-change review concern.
**Mitigation:** Call out that this change starts in the new preview version only.

query:
title: CASE 001004-version-property-decorator

question: change the visibility of property 'provisioningState' from Lifecycle.Read to Lifecycle.Read and Lifecycle.Create in version 2025-05-04-preview only

```
//main.tsp
@armProviderNamespace
@service(#{ title: "Widget" })
@versioned(Microsoft.Widget.Versions)
namespace Microsoft.Widget;

/** The available API versions. */
enum Versions {
  /** 2021-11-01 version */
  @armCommonTypesVersion(Azure.ResourceManager.CommonTypes.Versions.v5)
  v2021_11_01: "2021-11-01",

  /** 2025-05-04-preview version */
  @armCommonTypesVersion(Azure.ResourceManager.CommonTypes.Versions.v5)
  `2025-05-04-preview`,
}

//employee.tsp
/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```

ground_truth:
**Clarifying Questions**

- None.
**Understanding**
You want `EmployeeProperties.provisioningState` to stay `Read` in `2021-11-01`, but become `Read + Create` in `2025-05-04-preview` only.

**Key guidance to follow**

- For a decorator change across versions, use the official versioning pattern: `@removed` + `@added` + `@renamedFrom`, rather than trying to mutate one property in place.
- Because `2025-05-04-preview` is your latest version, keep the **current** property shape on the live property name `provisioningState`.
**Step-by-step plan**

1. In `employee.tsp`, replace the single `provisioningState` property with a versioned pair using the pattern from [Adding Decoration to an Existing Type](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis) and [ARM versioning guidance](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/versioning).
2. Keep the old behavior on a uniquely named legacy property for pre-`2025-05-04-preview` versions.
3. Put the new `Read + Create` behavior on the real `provisioningState` name for `2025-05-04-preview`.
**Diff outline**

```
// before
/** The status of the last operation. */
@visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
```

```
// after
/** The status of the last operation. */
@removed(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
@visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
@renamedFrom(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`, "provisioningState")
legacyProvisioningState?: ProvisioningState;

/** The status of the last operation. */
@added(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
@visibility(Lifecycle.Read, Lifecycle.Create)
provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
```
**Full updated `employee.tsp`**

```
/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @removed(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  @renamedFrom(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`, "provisioningState")
  legacyProvisioningState?: ProvisioningState;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @added(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read, Lifecycle.Create)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```
**Validation plan**

- Run:

```
tsp compile .
```

- Success looks like:

- `2021-11-01`: `provisioningState` is read-only behavior.
- `2025-05-04-preview`: `provisioningState` is allowed on create and visible on read.
**Risks & mitigations**

1. **ARM compliance risk** â€” `provisioningState` is usually service-managed. Only make it creatable if the RP truly accepts it.
2. **Wrong latest-shape modeling** â€” keep the new behavior on `provisioningState`, not the legacy alias.
3. **Emitter confusion** â€” use `@renamedFrom(...)` exactly as shown so older versions still emit `provisioningState`.

query:
title: CASE 001009-version-model-property-required

question: In the specification/widget/resource-manager/Microsoft.Widget/Widget project, make the `email` property required in EmployeeProperties only for version `2025-05-04-preview`.

```
/** Employee resource */
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
}

/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Email of employee */
  email?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```

ground_truth:
**Clarifying Questions**

- None. I can give the minimal TypeSpec change now.
**Understanding**

You want `EmployeeProperties.email` to stay optional in earlier API versions, but become required for `2025-05-04-preview` in this ARM TypeSpec project.

**Key guidance to follow**

- Use `@madeRequired(...)` for a property that becomes required in a specific version, per [Evolving APIs using the Versioning Library](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis/).
- If you mean **exactly one version only** and you have a later version after `2025-05-04-preview`, add `@madeOptional(...)` at the next version to revert it, per the same [versioning guidance](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis/).
- `@madeRequired` / `@madeOptional` come from the TypeSpec versioning library; the namespace must already be versioned with `@versioned(Versions)` as described in the [ARM versioning docs](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis/).
**Step-by-step plan**

1. In the file that declares `EmployeeProperties`, change `email` to a required property and add `@madeRequired(Versions.\`2025-05-04-preview`)`.
2. If there is a newer version and you mean **only** `2025-05-04-preview`, add `@madeOptional(Versions.<next-version>)` and keep `email?: string`.
**Diff outline**

If `2025-05-04-preview` is the **latest** version:

```
/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Email of employee */
  @madeRequired(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
  email: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```
If you mean **exactly that one version only** and there is a later version:

```
/** Email of employee */
@madeRequired(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
@madeOptional(Versions.`<next-version>`)
email?: string;
```
**Validation plan**

- Run the project build/emit for all versions and confirm:

- pre-`2025-05-04-preview`: `email` is optional
- `2025-05-04-preview`: `email` is required
- Success looks like generated OpenAPI showing `email` in `required` only for the intended version.
**Risks & mitigations**

1. **Latest-version mismatch** â€” If a newer version exists, use the second pattern.
2. **Missing versioning setup** â€” Ensure the namespace is already `@versioned(Versions)`.
3. **Decorator import confusion** â€” Verify the project already uses the TypeSpec versioning library before editing unrelated files.

query:
title: CASE 001010-version-model-property-removed

question: In the specification/widget/resource-manager/Microsoft.Widget/Widget project, remove the `department` property from EmployeeProperties only for version `2025-05-04-preview`.

```
/** Employee resource */
model Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties> {
  ...ResourceNameParameter<Employee>;
}

/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Department of employee */
  department?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```

ground_truth:
**Clarifying questions**

- None. Iâ€™m assuming `2025-05-04-preview` is the newest version in this spec. If you need `department` to disappear only in that preview and then come back in a later version, tell me the later version and Iâ€™ll give the add-back pattern.
**Understanding**
You want a versioned TypeSpec change in the Widget ARM spec so `EmployeeProperties.department` is not emitted for API version `2025-05-04-preview`, while leaving the rest of `EmployeeProperties` unchanged.

**Key guidance to follow**

- Use TypeSpec versioning on the **property itself**, not on `Employee` or the whole `EmployeeProperties` model. See [Versioning](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/versioning).
- For a property that should stop appearing starting in one version, use `@removed(...)` from the TypeSpec versioning library. See [How Versioning Works in TypeSpec](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/01-about-versioning).
- Do **not** change unrelated properties like `age`, `city`, `profile`, or `provisioningState`.
**Step-by-step plan**

1. In the file where `EmployeeProperties` is declared in `specification/widget/resource-manager/Microsoft.Widget/Widget`, add `@removed(Versions.v2025-05-04-preview)`directly above department. Pattern reference: [Versioning](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/versioning).
2. Leave `Employee is TrackedResource<EmployeeProperties>` unchanged, because the versioned behavior belongs on the property, not the resource wrapper. Guidance: [How Versioning Works in TypeSpec](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/01-about-versioning).
3. Recompile and confirm the emitted OpenAPI for `2025-05-04-preview` no longer contains `department`, while older versions still do. Validation guidance: [Versioning](https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/arm/versioning).
**Diff outline**

Before:

```
/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Department of employee */
  department?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```
After:

```
/** Employee properties */
model EmployeeProperties {
  /** Age of employee */
  age?: int32;

  /** City of employee */
  city?: string;

  /** Department of employee */
  @removed(Versions.`2025-05-04-preview`)
  department?: string;

  /** Profile of employee */
  @encode("base64url")
  profile?: bytes;

  /** The status of the last operation. */
  @visibility(Lifecycle.Read)
  provisioningState?: ProvisioningState;
}
```
**Validation plan**

1. Run compile:

```
tsp compile .
```

1. Check the generated `2025-05-04-preview` swagger/OpenAPI and verify `EmployeeProperties.department` is absent.
2. Check the prior version output and verify `EmployeeProperties.department` is still present.
3. Success looks like:

- no TypeSpec errors
- no `department` in `2025-05-04-preview`
- `department` still present in earlier versions
**Risks & mitigations**

1. **Risk:** `@removed` removes the property from that version onward.
**Mitigation:** Safe if `2025-05-04-preview` is the latest version; if a later version must restore it, model that explicitly in that later version.
2. **Risk:** Examples/tests still include `department` for `2025-05-04-preview`.
**Mitigation:** Update preview-version examples and scenario files after compile.
3. **Risk:** Service behavior still returns/accepts `department` in `2025-05-04-preview`.
**Mitigation:** Make sure the service contract matches the emitted spec before checking in.

query:
title: CASE 001011-version-model-property-renamed

question: In the specification/widget/resource-manager/Microsoft.Widget/Widget project, rename the `age` property to `employeeAge` in EmployeeProperties only for version `2025-05-04-preview`.

```
/** Employee resource */
